TopicTitle: [1.8-1.12] Kethane Plugin and Parts 0.11.0 - Now with background scanning.

Articles.Content:
I have released version 0.10.0 of Kethane. The main change from 0.9.13 is...

BACKGROUND SCANNING!!

That is, you can any number of scanning satellites scanning a body, or any number of bodies, and they will all update.

Also, the map update code has be optimized to not generate any garbage.

NOTE: As always, ElectricCharge is a concern. Stock RTGs (or anything that uses ModuleGenerator and produces only ElectricCharge without consuming any resources) and stock solar panels (ModuleDeployableSolarPanel, same resource constraints) are supported.

WARNING: if using solar panels, be sure to leave the scanner while in the sun, otherwise the panels will not work while the vessel is unloaded as Kethane simply records how much EC is being generated by the vessel's panels and then checks whether the scanner is in the sun or not.

Thank you very much!!

@Kerbinidiel: ok, this is actually good to know: it means it is some other mod. So... the question is which one.

Since Kethane+Kopernicus does work, we know it's one of the other mods. The quickest way to find out which is to do the following:

  1. Remove half of your mods (keeping Squad, Kethane and Kopernicus). (eg, mods starting with A-M)
  2. Test. If the grid works, add back half of the mods you removed (eg, mods starting with H-M), but if it fails, remove half the remaining mods (eg, N-T)
  3. Repeat, adding or removing half the number of mods each time until you find the one mod that causes problems.

In later steps, you either add half of those you have not tested yet, or remove half of the mods you last added. If you have 256 mods, this will take at most 8 steps, 7 for 128, 5 for 32...

[edit] it seems you have about 51 mods, so no more than 6 steps.

The problem is that you have a smaller monitor than taniwha.  He has the default kethane popup window set 1389 pixels to the right, so if your monitor is less than 1400 pixels wide you won't see the kethane window.

Solution: go into the GameData/Kethane directory and open the settings.cfg file.  Change the WindowLeft parameter to 500 then save the settings.cfg file. 

Taniwha, this is something you should probably change for future iterations of this mod.
